column2: Partly sunny and slight ripple on water.
Sunny- clear day. 3" chop on the water.
Partly sunny and 1" ripple on the water.
Fair amount of pollen on water. slight ripple on water.
Slight ripple on water. some pollen in water. sunny day.
3" ripple on water-recent rain-2 baby loons 6-26-96.
.4" of rain in early morning. partly sunny-3" ripple on water.
Water is very clear right now.
Clear-sunny-calm. about 30 common mergansers on lake.
Ice out on April 24- sunny clear and calm on 6/1/97 secchi was 8" from bottom.
Dead calm- sunny and clear- fair amount of pollen on lake.
Clear and sunny- 2" ripple on water.
Clear- sunny- slight ripple on water- no loon hatch this year.
Slightly hazy- slight ripple on water- no baby loons this year- very small duck hatch.
Sunny and clear with a slight ripple on the water
Sunny and clear with a slight ripple on the water
Sunny- clear- slight ripple- and ice out 4-7-98.
Sunny- partly cloudy- 1" ripple on water. rainy day before.
Sunny and clear. Pollen evident causing perception of 3.
Sunny and clear. 1" ripple on water. Rained during the night.
Sunny and clear. 1/2" ripple on water.
Sunny and clear. 1/2" ripple on water.
Sunny and clear. 1" ripple on water.
Sunny and clear. 2" ripple on water.
sunny last two weeks were windy with heavy waves
Sunny.  Last two weeks were windy with heavy waves.
Sunny- ripple on water. Pollen present

Hot weather rushed temps. To very warm levels.  Water brown tint.  Weeds below 10 feet.  Not many weeds in shallow bays.  Snails present in large numbers.  Tremendous numbers of small bluegills the past two years all over the lake.  Water feels very "soft".  I have concern over lack of fish habitat.   No weeds or cribs left.

Water very low.  Many underwater weeds.  We have been finding many dead suckers floating and on shore.  Lake is being taken over by bluegills- they are all oer.  2 loon families early - now only one chick.  Water temp- surface: 75 F.  21 feet down 72.5 F.  Graduated readings in between.  Water at least 18" low.
Lake very low (2.5-3).  Water clear.  2 adult loons plus baby on lake.  Mergansers and ducks present.
Lake very low.  All dead wood cover on shoreline above water level.  Low weeds in lake in places.
Lake continues to drop.  More weeds at 8-12 foot level.
Lake stays 3' or more lower than  normal.  No shoreline cover for fish.
Lake water level very low.  Beavers destroying shoreline trees.  Eagles chasing loons.
Lake level up 6" from fall level
Large amount of pine tree pollen in lake
Lake level down about 1 foot from spring
large ammount of pine tree pollen in water
Water clarity a bit off due to excessive rain runoff. lake level up aprox. 3" from last month.
Water appears murky due to rain runoff. Lake level up aprox 3" from last month
Lake level up aprox. 6" from previous month.
Water surface and shore are coved with snail shells. The ammount far exceeds previous years.
Lake levels back to Spring highs (june rain)
Ice out 5/7  Water level highest in last 10 years
Large amounts of tree pollen in water
Water level back to ice out depth
